headline: Valence Raises $50M Series B to Give Every Employee an AI Coach at Work
summary: Valence, the company behind Nadia, the world's first enterprise AI coach, today announced it has raised a $50 million Series B led by Bessemer Venture Partners. Sameer Dholakia, Partner at Bessemer, will join Valence's board, bringing both CEO operating experience and perspective from AI investments in Anthropic, Abridge, and EvenUp.

headline: For the First Time in 133 Years, Maxwell House Rebrands as "Maxwell Apartment"
summary: CHICAGO & PITTSBURGH, September 25, 2025--Today, Maxwell House rebrands to "Maxwell Apartment" to meet the needs of today’s consumer and remind fans the brand is synonymous with great tasting, affordable coffee. headline: Kraft Heinz pilots AI agent to streamline ketchup production

headline: In this economy!? Maxwell House rebrands as Maxwell Apartment
summary: The Kraft Heinz brand’s social-first campaign nods to the historically tough housing market by offering a 12-month “lease” on coffee for less than $40.
